one last hurrah to benefit the Blue Bear School of Music. All proceeds to benefit Blue Bear.
 
Please join Heather Combs and a fantastic crew of local musicians to celebrate the music community of the Bay Area and give a little back to help others. Music is such a cornerstone of all that we are so let’s come together one more time in 2016 to raise a glass, share some songs, have some laughs and tug at some heartstrings.
 
As Plato said, “Music gives soul to the universe, wings to the mind, flight to the imagination, and charm and gaiety to life and to everything.” Cheers to that. 
 
Performing December 1st will be Heather Combs, Brad Brooks, Tom Rhodes, Elliot Randall, Rick Hardin, Mike Gibbons, Melissa Phillips Deprato, Jesse Brewster, James Deprato, Kyle Caprista, Max Delaney, Kevin White, Jeff Bordes as well as some of the scholarship students and songwriting students at Blue Bear School of Music.

In her fifteen+ year career, she has shared the stage with many fantastic musicians such as Stevie Nicks, Tom Petty, Steve Earle, Sheryl Crow, Kasey Chambers, Todd Snider, Los Lobos and the Go-Gos. Heather's songs have been featured in hit TV shows such as ER and Grey's Anatomy. She is fiery, funny, intense and not afraid to take risks.
